Zest the @lime{1/2} and cut into wedges. Peel and grate the @garlic{1%clove}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}). Pop the @Sriracha Sauce{1}, @soy sauce{25%ml}, @ketjap manis{25%ml}, @honey{15%ml} and the lime zest into a #jug{} and mix well.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} over high heat. Once hot, add the @cooked pulled chicken{240%g} and @baby corn, greens & carrots{200%g} and stir fry until the vegetables are just tender and the chicken is piping hot, ~{3%minutes}. Add the garlic, @ginger puree{1/2%tsp} and sauce mixture and cook, stirring, for ~{1%minute}.

Meanwhile, cook the @steamed basmati rice{1%serving} to pack instructions. Divide the rice between plates and top with the stir fry. Serve with the lime wedges and enjoy!